Hello Brigss,

 From the documentation, 0 URI fetch status code means that fetch was 
never tried and it is  related to unsupported protocol or illegal URI. 
However, I have never seen this error code in a &quot;live&quot; crawl.

By default, Heritrix is configure to have 30 retires with 15 minutes 
wait periods between them. So, if you have a seed that has 
non-resolvable dns, it will take about 19 hours (30*15minutes) before 
crawler gives up on the dns fetch and moves on. This might explain the 
idle state that you are seeing.

Take care,
i.




